Description: Fragment of round handle to sharpish turn of Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Rectangular stamp. Clay fine pink-brown; traces of slip.
Curator's comments: Name Marsyas. Probably same as Petrie diary, p. 184, 8. Pencilled '53'. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0684.30.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0796)
